The paper discusses distributed data gathering in wireless sensor networks, which falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The paper also discusses the use of transforms for data gathering, which is a topic in Information Theory (cs.IT). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of wireless communications in data gathering, which falls under the category of Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the use of data correlation between nodes in the tree, which is a topic in Systems and Control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper proposes new wavelet transforms, which is a topic in Signal Processing (cs.SI).
